{"id":"cruse","term":"Cruse","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>A utensil; a flask or cup for holding water (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 26:11\">1 Sam. 26:11</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 26:12\">12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 26:16\">16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 19:6\">1 Kings 19:6</a>) or oil (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 17:12\">1 Kings 17:12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 17:14\">14</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 17:16\">16</a>). In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 14:3\">1 Kings 14:3</a> the word there so rendered means properly a bottle, as in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 19:1\">Jer. 19:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 19:10\">10</a>, or pitcher. In <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 2:20\">2 Kings 2:20</a>, a platter or flat metal saucer is intended. The Hebrew word here used is translated “dish” in 21:13; “pans,” in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 35:13\">2 Chr. 35:13</a>; and “bosom,” in <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 19:24\">Prov. 19:24</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 26:15\">26:15</a> (R.V., “dish”).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Samuel 26:11","1 Samuel 26:12","1 Samuel 26:16","1 Kings 19:6","1 Kings 17:12","1 Kings 17:14","1 Kings 17:16","1 Kings 14:3","Jeremiah 19:1","Jeremiah 19:10","2 Kings 2:20","2 Chronicles 35:13","Proverbs 19:24","Proverbs 26:15"]}